<!-- ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
  Schema: Area_2d_arm
   <express_ref linkend="area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm"/>
  ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm">
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Circular_area +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Circular_area">
 A <b>Circular_area</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/> containing the information necessary to determine the two-dimensional area of a circle. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Circular_area.radius">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Circular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Circular_area.centre">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>Circular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Elliptic_area +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area">

An <b>Elliptic_area</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/> that is the surface area of an ellipsis.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area.semi_axis_2">
specifies one role of the <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Elliptic_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area.semi_axis_1">
specifies one role of the <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Elliptic_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area.position">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Extended_basic_geometry:arm:Extended_basic_geometry_arm.Axis_placement_2d"/> for the <b>Elliptic_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Polygonal_area +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Polygonal_area">
A <b>Polygonal_area</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/> that has three distinct points as boundaries in the same plane. 
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Polygonal_area.bounds">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for the <b>Polygonal_area</b>. There shall be three or more  <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> for a <b>Polygonal_area</b>. No  <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Cartesian_point"/> shall be specified more than once as a <b>bounds</b> for a particular <b>Polygonal_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Primitive_2d +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d">
A <b>Primitive_2d</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Elemental_geometric_shape:arm:Elemental_geometric_shape_arm.Detailed_geometric_model_element"/>. A <b>Primitive_2d</b> is one of a <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Circular_area"/>, an <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Elliptic_area"/>, a <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area"/>, or a <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Polygonal_area"/>. It describes the surface area of a simple two-dimensional geometric shape.
<example>the surface area of a triangle is a <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/>, but the surface area of a pyramid is not a <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/>.</example>
</ext_description>
<!-- +++++++++++ Rectangular_area +++++++++++ -->
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area">
A <b>Rectangular_area</b> is a type of <express_ref linkend="Area_2d:arm:Area_2d_arm.Primitive_2d"/> that is the surface area of a rectangle.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area.y">
specifies one role of the <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Rectangular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area.x">
specifies one role of the <express_ref linkend="Value_with_unit_extension:arm:Value_with_unit_extension_arm.Length_data_element"/> for the <b>Rectangular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
<ext_description linkend="Area_2d_arm.Rectangular_area.position">
specifies the role of the <express_ref linkend="Extended_basic_geometry:arm:Extended_basic_geometry_arm.Axis_placement_2d"/> for the <b>Rectangular_area</b>.
</ext_description>
</ext_descriptions>

